6.ADC is an electronic device that converts continuous Analog signals into digital signals(binary data), 
  it does so by mapping voltages to values from 0 to 1023(in the case of 10 bit ADC like in arduino). 
  In Arduino Uno R3, Analog input pins (A0 to A5) function like ADC.
7.DAC is an electronic device that converts Digital signals(binary data) into a continuous analog voltage signal.
  It takes in a value(like from 0 to 255) and maps it to a voltage from 0 to 5 and outputs that voltage. 
  In arduino Uno R3 the GPIO pins 3,5,6,9,10,11 (the ones with the ~ sign before them) can function like a DAC by using PWM. 
  the other GPIO pins can also output analog signals, but they either output a voltage corresponding to the max voltage(5V) if value given in >0 , 
  else if value is 0, it outputs a 0 volt.

